text.text: Are stablecoins the future of money?

text:
- PayPal has been in the news with plans to issue its own stablecoin
- The stablecoin market has grown by 388% in 2021 and is expected to continue growing
- Stablecoins are pegged to underlying assets, such as gold or the US dollar, and are therefore less volatile than other digital assets
- Stablecoins enable quick and low-cost transactions and pay inflation-beating annual interest rates
- Increasing stablecoin regulation across the globe is set to create a more secure, level playing field
- Stablecoins allow digital asset owners to diversify portfolios, limit risk, and earn passive income

1. If you're a diamond and you staka stablecoins you get 13% paid in kind and 3% in yld

2. As described above, if you are only staking and not selecting "earn all in yld" you get the earnings as separated above. If you choose earn all in yld you get up to 18%

one last question:

if i want to lock my rewards for higher rates, is this possible?

got this, thanks 👍🏻

From the staked yld you can unstake to your wallet or you can lock.
I think you can only lock 1000 yld or more each time.
You have to enable it in the platform, but it is possoble
The 20% on locked is only valid this month. After it will be 12%

Staking and un staking is inmediate. However keep in mind that excessive manual stake/unstake actions can delay your rewards the next day. If your wish is to re-stake your rewards, please use the auto compound function within each fund. If you're investing usdt, enable it on both usdt and yld funds, you can unstake at any time if you wish to swap/withdraw a determined amount

You lock your yld at this time, but you first need to have said yld staked in order to be able to lock them

Do keep in mind that the 20% apy promotion on locked yld is available until March 1st, if you lock after that you'll get only 12% apy (which is still double of the base 6% you'd get if you're diamond and only staking)
Hope this makes sense! Please feel free to ask if you have any more questions

I'd like to invite you to read our Q4 report which touches on this subject, please read this excerpt:



Due-diligence and diversification

Over the fourth quarter, we strengthened our due-diligence processes further and we are pleased to share that both Kroll (a Duff & Phelps company) and PerForm Due Diligence (a JTC company) have been engaged by us to provide risk, governance, and continuous monitoring services on our behalf. 

Both of these organizations have extensive experience in providing these services and we are pleased that they have agreed to work with us as we expand our portfolio management capabilities.

External audit & proof of reserves

As previously stated in the Q3 report, we have engaged Armanino, one of the top 25 largest independent accounting and audit firms in the United States, and the global leader in digital asset audit solutions.

Armanino is engaged by many of the leading blockchain firms, including stablecoin issuers and wealth management platforms amongst its 7,000+ clients.

This engagement is for the purpose of offering Yield App’s customers, prospective customers, regulators, and business partners additional transparency and assurance over the assets held by us as reserves against outstanding customer liabilities.

We are pleased to share that this initial proof of reserves report was completed on January 24, 2022 using a ‘point in time’ methodology to determine the results, the full report published by Armanino can be read here.

We will continue to work with Armanino and other third-party accreditation service providers to release bi-annual independent reports across our group business activities as we grow.

For the full report, please visit:

KYC level 2 requires you to provide proof of residence, which cannot be over 3 months old and on which your name and residential address are clearly readable, which can be in the form of:

-Utility bills (including fixed line/cable/Internet bills)
-Bank statements (listing your residential address)
-Income tax statements from your country of residence
-Other recent government-issued residential statements and certificates (listing your current residential address)

messages.text:
📣 REMINDER 📣

Today is the last day to lock up your YLD for a huge 20% p.a.! From tomorrow, 1 March 2022, you will earn the standard 12% p.a. on new lock-ups. Don't miss your chance! 😲
Hello team, just simple question. Even if the market gets betters, rates can change?
The rates are adjusted due to market opportunities that are available for us to create stable and secure Interest
Is there a possibility that it will go higher during the month if the market conditions get better ?
What metrics do you take in consideration to drive your APY increase/decrease ? Anything we can follow on our end as well ?

It might be increased many months or years from now. Personally I don't see it. According to my experience with many  cefi companies , they have an easy time to reduce rates but a hard time to increase them even if the conditions allow it.

text: Personally I have seen in it in the past by

messages.text: Have seen them reduce yield before and then increase it when conditions are better

I have too, hence the question. I feel YA are taking an honest approach towards it, but would really like to have some kind of information on the metrics taken in consideration here to evaluate the trend it can potentially take in the coming months... just for the sake of it 😉

Yieldapp was and still is a very young company. You can bet that the early introduced rates were basically hurting the sustainability but was acting as a good marketing in order to get more users in the platform
From now on, if I see an increase in the rates, I will be positively surprised .
The bonus pay in YLD is for the marketing purposes, not the yield on other assets so there shouldn't be any extra on them, at least that's what is being told

I wouldn't think the yields that are now or were before were hurting the company because im sure that the funds deployed in various different defi protocols and liquidity pools are earning way more that 20% apy
They reduce it only to prevent any unnecessary possible risk and that's fine I think

text: But I do agree, that it would be nice to know more about the metrics that make
decide the rise or reduction of the yields on platform

messages.text: Guys it's hard to predict especially near future market sentiment but as soon as it improves Yield App will be looking for possibilities to increase rates while still providing maximum safety. We need nothing more than happy customers so you stay with us or even encourage your friends to consider joining us. 🔥
No, the rates are much lower in safe defi projects atm.
Hey T, I have deleted your message, let’s avoid advertising “competitors” here please.

text: At the moment it is a little bit unclear to me and would need some more transparency imo. Market neutral but funding rates matter? Still if market goes down then yield app adjusts rates and has done this before. So to me it seems only logical that
rates are very much market dependent. Would be great to know more though and best would be to be able to see this also on a simplified graphic/metric right on

site. Like just a big bar, at one end is "raise yield rates" other end "decrease of rates". It would move closer one or other end according to current conditions, updates daily (like fear and greed index). So maybe a dedicated page on

that explains how company earns the yield and then all info about decreasing and increasing rates and also history on all the past decreases and increases of the rates with dates and market snapshot and maybe even a little explanation there. This would surely be attractive to existing and new customers and be useful to crypto veterans and noobs alike.
